lyrics:
Dear Sathya Sai Baba I know You love me;
Awake or asleep there is nothing to fear,
I'm never alone for Sai Baba is here!

Then the sun will come your way.&nbsp;
If we learn how to give,&nbsp;
This is how we should live,&nbsp;
Give a little bit of love every day.&nbsp;

Give a little bit of kindness every day,&nbsp;
Then a smile will come your way.&nbsp;
If we learn how to give, this is how we should live.&nbsp;
Give a little bit of kindness every day.

Your coffers may be filled with gold,&nbsp;
But unless your heart is filled with kindness,&nbsp;
You'll be lonely when you grow old.&nbsp;
You may not have much money,&nbsp;
Your cupboards may be rather bare;&nbsp;
But if your heart is filled with kindness,&nbsp;
You'll be happy beyond compare.

And I'm very happy with that.&nbsp;
I may be short or I may be tall,&nbsp;
My body may be thin or fat.&nbsp;
But it really doesn't matter at all,&nbsp;
Because I am the way I am,&nbsp;
And I'm very happy with that.

But there's also something dark in there, ready to pull me down.&nbsp;
Once the light is shining, darkness will disappear;&nbsp;
And our life is filled with happiness, peace, love and good cheer.

Oh yes, every day.&nbsp;
You can count on me all the time (x3)&nbsp;
Oh yes, all the time.&nbsp;
I'll not let you down anyway (x3)&nbsp;
Oh no, not any way.

I will listen to my father's words,&nbsp;
For I know in this world there's no other,&nbsp;
Who will love me with a love so true.&nbsp;

I will always be kind to my mother,&nbsp;
And live up to my father's words,&nbsp;
For I know in this world there's no other,&nbsp;
Who will love me with a love so true.

If at first you don't succeed,&nbsp;
Try try, try again
Don't give up, don't despair,&nbsp;
In the end you'll win you'll win, in the end you'll win.&nbsp;

This world has many challenges&nbsp;
To meet them you need pluck.&nbsp;
You have to try so very hard,&nbsp;
You can't rely on luck.&nbsp;
So put your best foot forward,&nbsp;
And in your heart have faith,&nbsp;
That you can overcome each test,&nbsp;
And then you'll win the race.

That makes me want to know.
It's waiting there quite silently so one day I may grow.
It is the lamp of wisdom,&nbsp;
That's pure and shining bright,&nbsp;
That takes away the darkness,&nbsp;
Filling everything with light.

May we dare do what is right.&nbsp;
Let us fail not, Let us ail not,&nbsp;
Using all our strength and might.

In our lives are many problems,&nbsp;
Many obstacles in sight.&nbsp;
We must dare to, we must care to,&nbsp;
Go from darkness into light.

Helping in the hour of need bringing light, peace and joy.&nbsp;
We are brothers, sisters all in loving kindness,&nbsp;
Sharing with our fellow men, we are one small world.

So when they say do this, do that, I should do it without a fight.&nbsp;
Sometimes I may not listen, I may think it's unfair;&nbsp;
But what I must try to understand is, they do it because they care.

Are two words, are two words.&nbsp;
Please and Thank you are two words,&nbsp;
We should often use.&nbsp;

Can I help you, my dear friend?&nbsp;
My dear friend, my dear friend?&nbsp;
Can I help you, my dear friend?&nbsp;
I am always very ready.&nbsp;

Thank you for your kind words,&nbsp;
Kind words, kind words.&nbsp;
Thank you for your kind words,&nbsp;
You are very welcome.

To everyone you see.&nbsp;
Full of love and tolerance,&nbsp;
That's how the world should be.

You need a change of pace.&nbsp;
Take away that ugly frown,&nbsp;
Put a smile on your face.

Chorus:&nbsp;
Smile, smile, smile,&nbsp;
Smile the whole day through.&nbsp;
Smile smile, smile,&nbsp;
And the world is smiling too.

When you are unhappy,&nbsp;
And everything looks blue,&nbsp;
Don't give up and start to cry,&nbsp;
But this is what you do.

Chorus:&nbsp;
Smile, smile, smile,&nbsp;
Smile the whole day through.&nbsp;
Smile smile, smile,&nbsp;
And the world is smiling too.

So the light shines throughout the universe,&nbsp;
Spreading rays of love and peace and understanding,&nbsp;
That will help unite the brotherhood of man.&nbsp;
I am in the light, the light is in me, I am the light. (x2)&nbsp;

Let these eyes see the good in those around me,&nbsp;
And these ears listen only to what is true.&nbsp;
May this tongue of mine speak in moderation,&nbsp;
Words of wisdom that are full of sweetness too.&nbsp;
I am in the light, the light is in me, I am the light. (x2)&nbsp;

These two hands of mine must strive to serve my brothers,&nbsp;
And these feet should help me do what is right.&nbsp;
With a heart full of love and compassion,&nbsp;
See the world and all its beings bathed in light.
I am in the light, the light is in me, I am the light. (x2)

This should be our creed.&nbsp;
Serving others as we should,&nbsp;
In thought, word, and deed.&nbsp;
Life is not so easy,&nbsp;
But if we're to be free;&nbsp;
We must create unity, between the following three.&nbsp;

Think good, speak good, do good,&nbsp;
This should be our creed.&nbsp;
Serving others as we should,&nbsp;
In thought, word, and deed.

If we can work together, the I and you are We.
If we can work together, in peace and harmony (yes)&nbsp;
If we can work together, how happy we will be.
